               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gǝnzat “Book of the Funeral Ritual” (fols. 3ra-84rb)&#xD; -
                     Discourse of St Athanasius on death (fols. 15ra-17vb)&#xD; - Maṣḥaf za-waḍʾat
                     ʾǝm-ʾIyārusālem “Book that Came from Jerusalem” (fols. 17vb-23rb)&#xD; -
                     Mangada samāy “Journey to Heaven” (fols. 26va-38vb)&#xD; - Homily by ʾabbā
                     Salāmā, Metropolitan of Ethiopia (fols. 40rb-42rb)&#xD; - Homily by St Jacob of
                     Serug for the funeral of priests and deacons (fols. 62vb-66rb)&#xD; - Lǝfāfa
                     ṣǝdq “Bandlet of Righteousness” (fols. 73vb-77vb)&#xD; - Antiphons (Kǝśtata
                     ʾaryām, mawāśǝʾt) performed for the funeral of different categories of
                     Christians (fols. 79ra-80vb)&#xD; - Burāke za-ʾanǝst “Benediction of women”
                     (fols. 83ra-84rb)&#xD; &#xD; Additiones 1-3.</summary>
